WEBVTT

00:00.891 --> 00:03.570
Agent Lee?
Olivia Dunham.

00:03.594 --> 00:05.067
Previously on <i>Fringe...</i>

00:05.068 --> 00:06.702
What division are you in?

00:06.770 --> 00:08.988
I am not leaving here
without some answers.

00:10.407 --> 00:12.875
Sometimes answers...
lead to more questions.

00:16.480 --> 00:19.415
The timeline
has been rewritten.

00:19.466 --> 00:20.716
He was erased,

00:20.784 --> 00:24.420
and yet traces of him
continue to bleed through.

00:24.471 --> 00:25.888
There was a man
in the mirror!

00:25.955 --> 00:27.623
He was here,
and then he was gone.

00:27.674 --> 00:29.392
I saw him!

00:29.459 --> 00:31.126
What's with the redecoration?

00:33.063 --> 00:34.981
- Aah!
<i>I'm here, Walter.</i>

00:35.065 --> 00:36.732
<i>Right here.</i>

00:36.800 --> 00:38.367
<i>Please, help me.</i>

00:44.691 --> 00:46.075
<i>Walter?</i>

00:47.611 --> 00:51.364
<i>You didn't answer</i>
<i>my question.</i>

00:51.448 --> 00:52.782
<i>I asked</i>

00:52.833 --> 00:54.950
if you've been keeping up
with the new medication

00:55.002 --> 00:56.285
I prescribed for you.

00:56.336 --> 00:58.754
Yes.

00:58.822 --> 01:01.323
For the most part.

01:01.375 --> 01:06.095
With my own modifications,
of course.

01:06.162 --> 01:07.430
Why?

01:07.497 --> 01:10.566
Well, you just seem
a little bit distracted.

01:10.634 --> 01:13.803
Well, yes...
as you ask.

01:13.854 --> 01:19.275
You've come at an extremely
inopportune time.

01:19.342 --> 01:21.894
I'm in the middle
of some very important work,

01:21.978 --> 01:23.679
and I'm anxious to resume.

01:23.730 --> 01:25.281
I appreciate that,
Walter.

01:25.348 --> 01:28.451
But these monthly evaluations
are also important.

01:28.518 --> 01:29.452
Well, yes, I know.

01:29.519 --> 01:31.454
It was a condition
you imposed

01:31.521 --> 01:33.039
on my release
from St. Claire's.

01:33.123 --> 01:34.990
I mean personally
important.

01:35.058 --> 01:37.376
You were under my care
there for...

01:37.444 --> 01:39.779
most of your 17 years.

01:39.846 --> 01:43.132
These sessions allow me
to catch up with you,

01:43.200 --> 01:45.384
see how you're doing.

01:45.469 --> 01:47.053
Now...

01:47.137 --> 01:49.204
I've been perusing the latest
observational reports

01:49.256 --> 01:50.923
from the agents
assigned to you,

01:51.007 --> 01:56.195
and they mention certain
patterns of unusual behavior.

01:56.263 --> 02:00.032
Well, o-occasionally, I have
a unique way of doing things

02:00.100 --> 02:01.183
which can be misinterpret--

02:01.234 --> 02:02.852
Tell me about the mirrors.

02:02.903 --> 02:04.820
Mirrors?

02:04.888 --> 02:07.056
And the television?

02:07.124 --> 02:11.060
Virtually every reflective
surface in and around your lab

02:11.128 --> 02:13.245
has been covered
or obscured by you.

02:15.949 --> 02:18.734
Naturally,
I covered them up.

02:20.654 --> 02:22.237
I-it's an experiment
I'm conducting on--

02:22.289 --> 02:25.574
So this had nothing to do
with your lab being haunted.

02:25.625 --> 02:26.876
Beg your pardon?

02:26.927 --> 02:27.960
According to the report,

02:28.044 --> 02:30.463
you claimed on more than
one occasion

02:30.547 --> 02:33.716
to have seen a strange man
in the lab,

02:33.767 --> 02:35.601
a man no one else has seen,

02:35.685 --> 02:37.720
and that sometimes...

02:37.771 --> 02:39.588
the man speaks to you.

02:40.757 --> 02:42.942
Oh...

02:43.026 --> 02:45.928
just minor hallucinations,
of course,

02:45.979 --> 02:49.281
by my self-medication.

02:49.366 --> 02:52.067
That was weeks ago.
I-I'm much better now.

02:52.119 --> 02:55.871
So you haven't had any more
of these hallucinations since?

03:00.043 --> 03:01.777
No.

03:03.997 --> 03:06.799
Walter, it is important

03:06.883 --> 03:09.301
that you be completely
honest with me

03:09.386 --> 03:12.838
so that I can make an assessment
of your state of mind

03:12.923 --> 03:16.926
and I can make recommendations
for your continued care...

03:16.977 --> 03:19.461
Whatever that may be.

